question
Write a function differenceMaxMin that takes an array arr as an argument and returns 
the difference between the maximum and minimum value. If the array is empty, return null.
Example:
differenceMaxMin ([3, 4, 8, 1]) should return 7;
differenceMaxMin ([7, 7]) should return 0;
differenceMaxMin ([2]) must return 0;
the differenceMaxMin ([]) function must return null;

solution:

function differenceMaxMin(arr){
  let max = Math.max(...arr);
  let min = Math.min(...arr);
  if(arr.length === 0) return null;
  else
  return max - min;
}
